Driving you to the vet yesterday knowing you wouldn’t be coming home was beyond tough, and holding you till you took your last breath was the absolute worst. The weather was shit all day but for the 20-30 min we had you outside in the park for the procedure the sun came out just for you 🌞 I hope you felt at peace in my lap because that’s where you always liked to sit—despite the fact that you were once 140 lbs 🤣

I will treasure all the joy you brought to my cold heart who didn’t want a dog. You came into our lives unplanned but somehow it always felt like it was meant to be. You always joined us on our travels & were able to adapt & make friends wherever you went. 

I just can’t believe you’re gone. 

Thank you all for the texts & calls that I haven’t been able to return 💔 It is such a blessing to know that Logan was so loved. 

@robbietassaro made this vid & although it makes me cry, at least they are happy tears remembering all of the adventures we had with our best boy. 

Logan, to say you will be missed is an understatement.

Thank you @morristownanimalhospital for making a terrible life event somewhat bearable. 

I will love you Logan, forever.

Towards the end of my pregnancy I may have consumed a dozen #dunkindonuts a day 😅 —that I had delivered to my door 🤣🙏🏻
 
And then, after 26 hours of labor—no food— & no real progress in dilation (despite induction attempts) my Ma (who had been by my side for the entire 26 hours) stepped out to go get coffee & a donut @dunkin across the street from Wyckoff Heights Medical in #brooklyn— it was then the doctor came in & I had somehow dilated to a 10! And she started telling me to PUSH & I said no no no you have to go get my Ma she just stepped out for the first time!!!

Luckily Nino came back in right then & I told him to go get her, she thought he was joking because after a long 26 hours of waiting Penny was suddenly ready to make her debut!

Happy 81st birthday to the man, the myth, the legend that is my Papa! He was my first example of how great a man can be & I thank my lucky stars for him every day 🙏🏻

He can build anything, I repeat, anything— including my 1968 Fastback #Mustang 🥰 & is currently rebuilding a few other cars in the hot el Centro summer heat 😅

We love you so much Papa ♥️ My life wouldn’t be anything without you.

The only #weddingring I ever wanted on my finger was my Nana & Papa’s original #wedding ring that my Papa got for $400 back in 1961. I grew up loving the ring on my Nana’s finger, she always had the most beautiful hands, so soft, her perfect olive skin. 

For their 50th wedding anniversary she opted for a bigger Diamond ring— so when I finally decided to get married I knew what ring I wanted 🥰 and when I asked my Nana for it, she didn’t even think twice; she gave it to me instantly. And I am forever so grateful that she did because everyday I look at it on my hand & think of her ♥️ …although my hands aren’t nearly as dainty 😂 (insert Seinfeld #manhands joke here lol)

When Nino & I decided to get married in #brooklyn during COVID I knew (sadly) that my Nana & Papa wouldn’t be able to come— so I packed up my car & drove solo from NYC to San Diego to get my wedding dress with my Nana & Ma 💕 And before I left back east we took photos together of me in my dress as if they were at the wedding 🥹

And of course, they were there in spirit (and cardboard cutout). 

♥️
